reviews.comment: My experience with virtual physical therapy at Alliance was incredibly positive. It was very easy to access, convenient, effective, and perhaps most importantly, it was the most affordable option I have found. The pricing was absolutely straightforward, fair, and I knew exactly when and how much I would be billed for these services. My therapist, Katie, was excellent. She was knowledgeable, communicative, and very effective. She gave me a wide variety of exercises and stretches that provided relief, answered all my questions, and was just overall very helpful and informative. After just a few sessions, I felt noticeable improvement and significant reduction in the chronic neck and shoulder pain that has been bothering me for the better part of a year. Now, my nagging pain is gone and I both feel better physically, and feel like I have a better understanding overall of the causes of my discomfort and how to best manage it now and in the future. I would recommend this service to anyone who has been struggling with pain but can't find an affordable or convenient option. I truly can't say enough good things about it.
